FT  06 SEP 94 / Letters to the Editor: Omission
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr BEN PIMLOTT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I have just seen Alan Clark's hilariously splenetic piece about my
Frustrate Their Knavish Tricks (Books, August 27/28), in which I am
presented as a kind of ageing and illiterate Dave Spart, whose extreme
leftwing views belong in the 1970s. The only puzzling thing is that the many
quotes-out-of-context in Lord Clark's article do not include my sole
reference to him. On the very first page of the book I describe the Tory
ex-minister as a former MP 'of indisputably blimpish proportions' who has
'written a book review backing a suggestion that Winston Churchill ruined
the country'.
But then again, he was probably right. If he had mentioned it, some
unsporting socialist bounder might have accused him of tit-for-tat
reviewing.
Ben Pimlott,
9 Milner Place,
London N1 1TN
