</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Germany's record lottery jackpot failed to find a winner for the tenth week,
rising to DM42m (Pounds 17.4m) ahead of the next draw on Saturday. Lottery
officials said yesterday no winning card had been turned in for the latest
weekly draw, which would have netted a top prize of over DM35m. Ten players
each won DM1.9m for getting six of 49 numbers right, but winning the jackpot
requires seven numbers. Germans have succumbed to lottery fever as the
jackpot has mounted and bought more than 30m cards last week, with some help
from eager players who come over from neighbouring countries.
