FT  06 SEP 94 / Brussels probes VW deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission said yesterday it would investigate a plan by
Volkswagen to acquire Sachsische Automobilbau (SAB), a former East German
state-owned car factory, from the Treuhand privatisation agency. Brussels
said the German carmaker's bid for 87.5 per cent of SAB's shares could fall
under its merger rules, but reserved a final decision. In July, it cleared
the way for VW to receive around DM1.2bn in subsidies toward its investment
in SAB. The Commission has four weeks to decide whether the link-up could
harm competition. If it finds 'serious doubts' about the transaction, it
must launch a deeper probe.
