parliament, where the governing Socialists have a clear absolute majority,
has already voted in a separate case to try Mr Mitsotakis on charges of
illegal wiretapping. Mr Mitsotakis is accused of accepting Dollars 22.5m in
bribes in the sale of the state-run Heracles cement company to Italy's
Calcestruzzi Cement and Greece's National Bank for Dollars 225m.
