FT  05 SEP 94 / Emerging Markets: News round-up - Jordan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Amman share market was depressed last week by plans for a capital gains
tax on the share dealing of finan- cial institutions. On Tuesday, most
shares plunged to the 5 per cent daily price limit imposed to stabilise
fluctuations. On Wednesday, however, the general price index ended weekly
trading only 0.55 down on the day at 147.12.
A feared steep fall in volume and prices was averted after investors decided
the proposals were unenforceable at any time in the near future, and that
they still had to be debated before becoming law.
