<TEXT>
Sir, Mrs Florence Gilkes did indeed see a button A and B payphone on the
island of Soay on August 1 (Letters, September 1). However, BT's large
investment programme caught up with the kiosk on August 22, when the old
mechanism was replaced by a modern unit. Papa Stour 224 in the Shetland
Isles was similarly updated on August 25, thus assuring it of its place in
telecommunications history as the UK's last working public button A and B
payphone.
